:'''Gunn:''' Yes, you are right. Some things are better left to a youngster like you.
:'''Gunn:''' You see, I'd like you to be a teacher for an android. Teach her about life and how to handle her relationship with others.
:<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_300052201_10-->
:<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_300052201_10-->
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} You're more learned about these. Why not teach her yourself?
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_300052305-->
::'''Gunn:''' I did, but the result was not ideal. Although Prototype 157 I made earlier had independent thinking capability to a certain degree, I couldn't answer her questions about our world.
::'''Gunn:''' I can teach her theories, but the world is ever-changing. There are things that only you young people can keep up with.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} The space station is teeming with young people.
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_300052308-->
::'''Gunn:''' Not everyone is willing to deal with an android. Besides... They are only willing to teach her things related to scientific research. When it comes to teaching her facts of life, you are a better candidate than them.
:<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_300052309-->
:<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_300052309-->
:'''Gunn:''' I've heard of your deeds in the space station. In my opinion, you're among the best of us.
:'''Gunn:''' And I just made Prototype 159... Although I have limited her capacity to think independently, she learns better and faster than most.
:'''Gunn:''' Without a "decent person" to show her the way and shape her personality to be in line with human moral standards, I dare not let her delve into advanced theories... If she develops any deviant thoughts, the consequences could be unimaginable.
:<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_300052201_20-->
:<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_300052201_20-->
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Aren't you worried I might lead her astray?
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_300052313-->
::'''Gunn:''' No, I have confidence in you. Besides, I am just asking you to show her what our daily life is like. Things like entertainment and hobbies. I don't think there will be any big problems.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} I don't know what I can teach her...
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_300052315-->
::'''Gunn:''' Simple. Tell her about the foods and drinks you like, or what you do when you have spare time. She'll turn these into her own knowledge.
:<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_300052316-->
:<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_300052316-->
:'''Gunn:''' Tell her what kind of person she should be, things to do for fun, what we do every day... Tell her all you know and she'll pick them up one by one.
