::{{DIcon|Talk}} Is Sheila doing well?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_500204304-->
:::'''Gunn:''' It depends on how you define "well."
:::'''Gunn:''' She doesn't remember what happened before and doesn't have anything to worry about, so I'd say she is "doing well."
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} I think I saw Sheila again.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_500204307-->
:::'''Gunn:''' Yes. She's a guide in the Department of Galactic Geopolitics, and the Department can't function without her.
:::'''Gunn:''' But you probably also know she is no longer Prototype 157.
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} What are your plans?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_500204310-->
:::'''Gunn:''' I'm getting old, and I don't have much that I want anymore. A peaceful life is good enough.
:::'''Gunn:''' I might train some students if I have the time. I heard... that some young researchers are apparently very interested in working on androids.
:::'''Gunn:''' Given an opportunity, I would like to teach them a thing or two... Ahh, after all, everyone has regrets.
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
